<br>
Monks weren't meant to be pullers.  They're supposed to be damage dealers.  They have an armor restriction for a reason.. nothing over 1 lb.  Why?  Because they're supposed to do mega damage, and get beaten down severely if they tank even for a minute.  They should do more damage then a rogue if the rogue and monk stand facing a mob, but a skilled backstabbing rogue should be able to outdamage a monk.  Thats how the classes were designed.  Monks became pullers because of feign death.  Makes sense to me.. but don't expect the class to get upgrades to armor so that they can pull better.. they should have made SK's take the role of puller from monks by making it a skill instead of a spell.  That would have fixed that problem.<br>
<br>
Mod rods are severely broken.  I've played a cleric in a chain.. you have infinite mana regardless of your equipment.  (As long as you're good enough to be raiding where ever you're at that is.. you won't see a cleric in a chain in Vex Thal if he's barely gotten any Kunark armor yet.)  I don't even understand why they would put them in the game after nerfing the mana stone.  Stupid in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Rogues should not be getting any upgrades to anything, poison included.  Leave them the hell alone, they're doing too much damage with 16 damage piercers as it is.  They're gonna end up throwing more stuff out of whack with these new poisons.<br>
<br>
Manaburn.. good riddance.  People have gone over why, so I don't have to.  Nuff said.<br>
<br>
Warriors will get more hp in pop.  The changes to cleric CH will only matter then.  I still disagree with giving druids and shamans that good of a heal.  3k heal is too much for a druid.  2k tops.  They have enough of a plethra of uses on a raid.  If you disagree, too bad.<br>
<br>
They should make the cast time on feign death instant for SK's, and totally blow away all this SUPER armor that monks get.  They put that weight restriction in there for a reason.  They're not supposed to tank at all.<br>
<br>
As for mages, I have to agree with the whole idea that they should be doing second best damage to wizards and have all their other stuff as additional advantages.  Pets are nice, but not for raiding.  Having an advantage doesn't necessarily mean it has to be an advantage in all situations.  You can't say &quot;Yeah its nice for grouping and or soloing, but it sucks at a raid!&quot; because the fact is, the advantage is an advantage for a certain situation.  Maybe not the one you want it to be an advantage for, but it doesn't maek it any less of an advantage.<br>
<br>
Hopefully they will get around to some of the other overpowered classes and situations in EQ.  And perhaps stop making it so damn easy? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127902">Jaeron -Shadowstalker</a>, Merc for Hire, at your service. 
Friendly Neighborhood Mercenary - Elitists and Vagrants</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uunnone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unnone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/10/02 9:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: nerfs on the way</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, but any class with a level 49 pet can't be as strong as other classes in other areas.  Your pet tanks for you.  He does wicked,manaless damage.  And you want nukes comparable to a *wizard*?  Get off the crack pipe.  Mages do very respectable damage.  They have very nice nukes.    <br>
<br>
In the short run, no one should even come close to a wizard's damage.  Wizards give up everything for nukes.  Everything.  Mages get focus items they can summmon, that improve their performance above and beyond drop items, boosting their spell performances;  they get a pet that has more hp than lots of warriors.  They have nukes that, combined with their pet, make for very formidable damage dealers.  I've seen mages afk-xp in more than one situation, before the nerfs.  And you want fries with that?<br>
<br>
Wizards get dds.  And TPs.   Lets cancel the focus items with tps.   So now...Where's my 2300hp rune with 30pnt ds and +500 offense that lets me tank a mob and prevents spell interrupts?<br>
<br>
Wizard goes oom, he is toast.   Mage goes oom, he meds while his pet saves his ass.  Don't start with the 'my nukes should be 100hp less damage than a wizard's nukes' line of jive.  That's like a bard asking for warrior damage in melee.<br>
